msgstr "Monks’ Suspension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Attakā­ma­pāri­cari­ya­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "4. The training rule on fulfilling one’s own desires"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.132"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.222"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.4.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.4.1.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1180"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anātha­piṇḍi­"
"kassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī sāvatthiyaṃ kulūpako hoti, bahukāni "
"kulāni upasaṅkamati."
msgstr ""
"At that time Venerable Udāyī was associating with and visiting a number of "
"families in Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā itthī matapatikā abhirūpā hoti dassanīyā "
"pāsādikā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī pubbaṇ­ha­samayaṃ nivāsetvā patta­cīvara­mādāya yena "
"tassā itthiyā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"One morning Udāyī robed up, took his bowl and robe, and went to the house of "
"a beautiful widow,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on the prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "Atha kho sā itthī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "That woman approached Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ itthiṃ āyasmā udāyī dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi "
"samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr "Udāyī then instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā itthī āyasmatā udāyinā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā "
"samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And she said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "“vadeyyātha, bhante, yena attho."
msgstr "“Venerable, please say what you need."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid ""
"Paṭibalā mayaṃ ayyassa dātuṃ yadidaṃ "
"cīvara­piṇḍa­pāta­se­nāsa­na­gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khā­ran”ti."
msgstr "I’m able to give robe-cloth, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1181"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid ""
"“Na kho te, bhagini, amhākaṃ dullabhā yadidaṃ "
"cīvara­piṇḍa­pāta­se­nāsa­na­gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khārā."
msgstr "“It’s not hard for us, Sister, to get those requisites."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid "Api ca yo amhākaṃ dullabho taṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "Give instead what’s hard for us to get.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "“Kiṃ, bhante”ti?"
msgstr "“What’s that, Venerable?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid "“Methunadhamman”ti."
msgstr "“Sexual intercourse.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid "“Attho, bhante”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it wanted now, Venerable?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid "“Attho, bhaginī”ti."
msgstr "“It is, Sister.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.223"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.18"
msgid "“Ehi, bhante”ti,"
msgstr "“Come, Venerable,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.19"
msgid "ovarakaṃ pavisitvā sāṭakaṃ nikkhipitvā mañcake uttānā nipajji."
msgstr ""
"and she entered her bedroom, took off her clothes, and lay back on the bed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.20"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī yena sā itthī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā—"
msgstr "Udāyī approached her and spat out,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.21"
msgid "“ko imaṃ vasalaṃ duggandhaṃ āmasissatī”ti,"
msgstr "“Who would touch this foul-smelling wretch!”"

#. VAR: niṭṭhubhitvā → nuṭṭhuhitvā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.22"
msgid "niṭṭhubhitvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "and he departed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1182"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.23"
msgid "Atha kho sā itthī ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "That woman then complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.24"
msgid "“alajjino ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dussīlā musāvādino."
msgstr "“These Sakyan recluses are shameless and immoral liars."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.25"
msgid ""
"Ime hi nāma dhammacārino samacārino brahmacārino saccavādino sīlavanto "
"kalyāṇadhammā paṭijānissanti."
msgstr ""
"They claim to live according to the Truth, to be celibate and of good "
"conduct, to be truthful, moral, and of good character."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.26"
msgid ""
"Natthi imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ natthi imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ "
"naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, kuto imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ kuto imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ,"
msgstr "But they don’t have the qualities of an ascetic or a brahmin;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.27"
msgid "apagatā ime sāmaññā apagatā ime brahmaññā."
msgstr "they’ve lost the plot."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.28"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma samaṇo udāyī maṃ sāmaṃ methunadhammaṃ yācitvā, ‘ko imaṃ "
"vasalaṃ duggandhaṃ āmasissatī’ti niṭṭhubhitvā pakkamissati."
msgstr ""
"How can the ascetic Udāyī request sexual intercourse from me, but then spit "
"out, ‘Who would touch this foul-smelling wretch!’ and depart?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.29"
msgid "Kiṃ me pāpakaṃ kiṃ me duggandhaṃ,"
msgstr "What’s bad about me? How am I foul-smelling?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.1.30"
msgid "kassāhaṃ kena hāyāmī”ti?"
msgstr "In what way am I inferior to whom?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1183"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.4.1.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1184"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid "Aññāpi itthiyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "Other women, too, criticized him"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "“alajjino ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dussīlā musāvādino … pe …"
msgstr "in the same way,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma samaṇo udāyī imissā sāmaṃ methunadhammaṃ yācitvā, ‘ko imaṃ "
"vasalaṃ duggandhaṃ āmasissatī’ti niṭṭhubhitvā pakkamissati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "Kiṃ imissā pāpakaṃ kiṃ imissā duggandhaṃ, kassāyaṃ kena hāyatī”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ itthīnaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ."
msgstr "and the monks heard them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.224"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī mātugāmassa santike attakā­ma­pāri­cari­yāya "
"vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Udāyī commend the fulfilling of his own desires in the "
"presence of a woman?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.133"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1185"></a> 
#. VAR: Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato → atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato (sī1, syā1-3, pā1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "Those monks rebuked Udāyī in many ways and then told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master had the Order of monks assembled and questioned Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, mātugāmassa santike attakā­ma­pāri­cari­yāya "
"vaṇṇaṃ bhāsasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Is it true, Udāyī, that you commended the fulfilling of your own desires in "
"the presence of a woman?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid ""
"“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ "
"akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“It’s not suitable, foolish man, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a "
"recluse, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmassa santike attakā­ma­pāri­cari­"
"yāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissasi."
msgstr ""
"How can you commend the fulfilling of your own desires in the presence of a "
"woman?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid ""
"Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, aneka­pariyā­yena virāgāya dhammo desito no sarāgāya "
"… pe …"
msgstr ""
"Haven’t I given many teachings for the sake of dispassion, not for the sake "
"of passion …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid "kāma­pari­ḷāhā­naṃ vūpasamo akkhāto?"
msgstr "for the stilling of the fevers of sense desire?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1186"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu otiṇṇo vipariṇatena cittena mātugāmassa santike "
"attakā­ma­pāri­cari­yāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyya—"
msgstr "‘If a lustful monk encourages a woman to satisfy his own needs:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.225"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.21"
msgid ""
"‘etadaggaṃ, bhagini, pāricariyānaṃ yā mādisaṃ sīlavantaṃ kalyāṇadhammaṃ "
"brahmacāriṃ etena dhammena paricareyyāti methunu­pasaṃ­hi­tena’, "
"saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sister, she provides the highest service who in this way satisfies one like "
"me, who is virtuous, celibate, and of good character,” and if it is a "
"reference to sexual intercourse, he commits an offense entailing "
"suspension.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs1.2.22"
msgid "(<em>4</em>:<strong>8</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.4.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1187"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1188"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Otiṇṇo nāma"
msgstr "Lustful:"

#. </span>
#. I have rendered <i lang="pli">otiṇṇo vipariṇatena cittena</i> with the single word “lustful.” This means that the definition for <i lang="pli">vipariṇataṃ</i> is missing from my translation. Here is the Pali, followed by a translation: <i lang="pli">Vipariṇatanti rattampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Duṭṭhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Mūḷhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Api ca rattaṃ cittaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetaṃ vipariṇatanti</i>; “distorted: a mind with desire is distorted, a mind with anger is distorted, a confused mind is distorted. But in this case ‘distorted’ refers to a mind with desire.”
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "sāratto apekkhavā paṭi­baddha­citto."
msgstr "having lust, longing for, in love with."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1189"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Vipariṇatanti"
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.9"
msgid ""
"rattampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ, duṭṭhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ, mūḷhampi cittaṃ "
"vipariṇataṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Api ca rattaṃ cittaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetaṃ vipariṇatanti."
msgstr ""

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1190"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Mātugāmo nāma"
msgstr "A woman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "manussitthī, na yakkhī, na petī, na tiracchānagatā."
msgstr ""
"a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.13"
msgid ""
"Viññū paṭibalā subhā­sita­dub­bhāsi­taṃ duṭṭhul­lā­duṭṭhul­laṃ ājānituṃ."
msgstr ""
"She understands and is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, "
"what is lewd and what is not lewd."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1191"></a>
#. I have rendered <i lang="pli">mātugāmassa santike</i>, “in the presence of a woman,” simply as “woman.” Since woman has already been defined above, this definition falls away in my translation. Here is the Pali of the missing part, followed by a translation: <i lang="pli">Mātugāmassa santiketi mātugāmassa sāmantā, mātugāmassa avidūre.</i>; “in the presence of a woman: near a woman, close to a woman.”
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Mātugāmassa santiketi"
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "mātugāmassa sāmantā, mātugāmassa avidūre."
msgstr ""

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1192"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "Attakāmanti"
msgstr "His own needs:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "attano kāmaṃ attano hetuṃ attano adhippāyaṃ attano pāricariyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"his own sense desires, for the sake of himself, aiming at himself, "
"satisfying himself."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1193"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss4:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "Etadagganti"
msgstr "The highest:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
